- There are competing incentives in the choices that you make; if you're a manager then buying a 'conventional' stock is safe for your career even if it underperforms. p287
- Disparity between buying and selling a 1/1000 risk of immediate death is very large. p288
- Interesting discussion on intentionally limiting your options; instant gratification vs long term thinking . p291
- People overweigh new information. - p293
- Endowment Effect - once you own something you value it more than when you didn't own it. p295

